Total: 42   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">All out Arderial power. Yeah. ^.^<br>
<br>
Starting with Delia, you&#39;ll want to set out a Vellup or two, snatching an Elder Vellup with the last one. Depending who I might be facing, I tend to keep one of the Vellup&#39;s in the deck, to be snatched by one of them as they recur from the Discard pile. Arderian Guard-Wings are insanely important in this deck, as spells like Wildfire and Thunderquake can completely ruin your day.<br>
<br>
If Delia is defeated, Shimmer comes out next.. If you feel that the first Magi might fall, be sure to keep a few creatures in your hand as Shimmer dosn&#39;t start with any. Unless you are in danger of being overrun, or facing the threat of mass-removal, try to get her to 0 energy at the end of your turn. Not only will the opposing creatures take a damage, yours will gain 2 energy.<br>
<br>
Last one up is the Lady of Xyx&#39;s... Ora. With her, any Xyx minor she plays can pump itself up for 2 every turn. Toss in the Sorreah&#39;s Dreams on any one of the Xyx types, and you&#39;ve got some fun. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
